rComments: She a great professor with a subject that is hard to teach to already developed students, specially where English is a second language. rComments: Third time having a course with her. She's amazing in teaching and engaging students, BUT she can be a hard marker. Her quizzes/final can be challenging. In order to be successful in her classes, you MUST read all the readings ahead of time. DO NOT cram. There's just too many theories, examples, and definitions to memorize. Start ahead of time.

She's a tough professor who expects you to work very hard. DO NOT leave the readings until the week before the exam; you will want to kill yourself.  Assignments are frequent, but there is no midterm. There is absolutely no guessing on her final. If you don't study, you will fail. Powerpoints are useless and there's attendance, so go to class too.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Get ready to read', 'So many papers']

rComments: She doesn't baby students. If you don't put in the effort, she won't reward you. You have to put in the work to get the mark. Even with all the effort, she's still a tough grader, and so are the TA's. She gives lots of readings, and her tests are very specific to the reading. Know them by heart.
she's really helpful and approachable, but she is a tough grader
